'''Rick Willis''' is an [[American football]], [[baseball]], and [[softball]] coach.  He is currently the head football coach at [[Wartburg College]] in [[Waverly, Iowa]], a position he held from 1997 to 2005 and resumed again in 2008.  Willis served as the head baseball coach at [[Wittenberg University]] in [[Springfield, Ohio]] from 1991 to 1996, compiling a record of 150&ndash;85.  He also coached the softball team at Wartburg for one season in 2003, tallying a mark of 38&ndash;10.

